Low pathogenic avian influenza (poultry), China (People's Rep. of)
------------------------------------------------------------------
Information received on 04 Apr 2013 from Dr Zhang Zhongqui, Director General, China Animal Disease Control Centre, Veterinary Bureau, Ministry of Agriculture, Beijing, China (People's Rep. of).

Summary:
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 04 Apr 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 04 Apr 2013
Report date: 04 Apr 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 04 Apr 2013
Reason for notification: New strain of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: Sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: Low pathogenic avian influenza virus
Serotype: H7N9
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (basic), Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to: the whole country
Related reports:
Immediate notification (04 Apr 2013)
Follow-up report No. 1 (05 Apr 2013)

New outbreaks (1):
Outbreak 1: Huhuai agricultural products wholesale market, Songjiang, Shanghai, Shanghai
Date of start of the outbreak: 04 Apr 2013
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Not applicable
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 20536 / 8 / 0 / 20536 / 0
Affected population: A pigeon for consumption in a wholesale market. 7 samples from chickens and 1 sample from the environment

Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 20536 / 8 / 0 / 20536 / 0

Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Birds / 0.04 percent / 0.00 percent / 0.00 percent / 100.00 percent
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection
* Unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: Up to date there is no evidence that China human H7N9 cases come from this pigeon case. Further investigations are on-going

Control measures:
Measures applied:
* Control of wildlife reservoirs
* Quarantine
* Movement control inside the country
* Screening
* Zoning
* Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s)
* Dipping / Spraying
* No vaccination
* No treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied:
* Stamping out

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Harbin veterinary research institute, Chinese academy of agricultural sciences (OIE's Reference Laboratory) / Birds / gene sequencing / 04 Apr 2013 / Positive
Harbin veterinary research institute, Chinese academy of agricultural sciences (OIE's Reference Laboratory) / Birds / haemagglutination inhibition test (HIT) / 4 Apr 2013 / Positive
Harbin veterinary research institute, Chinese academy of agricultural sciences (OIE's Reference Laboratory) / Birds / pathogen isolation by egg inoculation / 04 Apr 2013 / Positive
Harbin veterinary research institute, Chinese academy of agricultural sciences (OIE's Reference Laboratory) / Birds / reverse transcription - polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 04 Apr 2013 / Positive

Future Reporting: The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

