Date: 5 Apr 2013
<Source: South China Morning Post [edited]
http://www.scmp.com/news/china/article/1208128/shanghai-tests-show-h7n9-bird-flu-chickens>


"The ministry said last night [4 Apr 2013] that 10 chicken samples from two markets in the Minhang district of Shanghai and at the Huhuai Farm Products Market in
the adjacent Songjiang district had tested positive for H7N9.

The virus was also found in 2 pigeon samples and 7 environmental
samples collected from these markets, out of a total 738 samples tested."

